    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - HIGH-PRESSURE OIL PUMP - Cleaning and Inspection</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26511.3">
        <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
        <svcproc id="s26511.3.1" svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
            <title>High-pressure Oil Pump Cover</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean old sealant residue from the pump cover, crankcase cover, and rear cover mating
                    areas.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the cover for the high-pressure oil pump assembly, the crankcase cover, and
                    sealing surfaces of rear cover for dirt, raised metal or indications of seal failure. Correct
                    defects, if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and inspect the IPR valve for the following:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>O-ring sealing surfaces for dirt, raised metal or other indications of seal failure.
                            Correct defects, if necessary.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>The electrical connector. See "Engine Electrical" for inspection criteria.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Valve openings for dirt or debris. Investigate causes and correct, if necessary.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
